<song>
    <title>84 - God the Omnipotent</title>
    <author>Henry F. Chorley (1808-1872) (1842)</author>
    <copyright></copyright>
    <presentation>V1 V2 V3 V4</presentation>
    <capo print="true" sharp="true"></capo>
    <tempo></tempo>
    <ccli></ccli>
    <theme>God the Father: Majesty and Power of God</theme>
    <user1></user1>
    <user2></user2>
    <user3></user3>
    <lyrics>[V1]
 God the Omnipotent! King,
 who ordainest
 Great winds Thy clarions,
 the lightnings Thy sword;
 Show forth Thy pity
 on high where Thou reignest,
 Give to us peace,
 O most merciful Lord.
 
[V2]
 God the all merciful!
 earth hath forsaken
 Thy precepts holy,
 and slighted Thy word;
 Bid not Thy wrath
 in its terrors awaken;
 Give to us peace,
 O most merciful Lord.
 
[V3]
 God the all righteousness One!
 man hath defied Thee;
 Yet to eternity
 standeth Thy word;
 Falsehood and wrong
 shall not tarry beside Thee;
 Prosper the right,
 O most merciful Lord.
 
[V4]
 So shall we render
 Thee thankful devotion,
 For Thy deliverance
 from peril and sword,
 Singing in chorus
 from ocean to ocean,
 “Thine is the power
 and the glory, O Lord.”</lyrics>
    <hymn_number>84</hymn_number>
